<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="12" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1436,1164,1333]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,499,1164,1189]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Distribution and habitat.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[507,753,1164,1189]" class="Reptilia" family="Dactyloidae" genus="Anolis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="philopunctatus">
<emphasis box="[507,753,1164,1189]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Anolis philopunctatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is endemic to central Amazonia, with distribution delimited by the Amazon, Negro and Trombetas Rivers (southwestern 
<collectingCountry box="[834,915,1201,1226]" name="Guyana" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Guiana</collectingCountry>
region—Fig. 
<number box="[1073,1088,1201,1226]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" value="5.0">5</number>
), until now only in the state of Amazonas, 
<collectingCountry box="[293,365,1236,1261]" name="Brazil" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Brazil</collectingCountry>
. It is also present in the Anavilhanas archipelago, in the lower Negro River. 
<taxonomicName class="Reptilia" family="Dactyloidae" genus="Anolis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="philopunctatus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Anolis philopunctatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is arboreal and diurnal, inhabits primary terra firme forest, where it is found on trunks of large trees, 
<number box="[151,192,1308,1333]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" value="4.0" valueMax="6.0" valueMin="2.0">2–6</number>
meters above ground (
<bibRefCitation author="Rodrigues" box="[449,633,1308,1333]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" refString="Rodrigues, M. T. (1988) A new anole of the punctatus group from central Amazonia (Sauria, Iguanidae). Papeis Avulsos de Zoologia, 36, 333 - 336." type="journal article" year="1988">
Rodrigues 
<number box="[573,633,1309,1333]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" value="1988.0">1988</number>
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
